.TH CHOWN 1 "2026-05-18" "OurOS" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
chown \- change file owner and group
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B chown
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIOWNER\fR][:\fIGROUP\fR] \fIFILE\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Change the user and/or group ownership of each FILE to OWNER and/or GROUP.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
Operate on files and directories recursively.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Output a diagnostic for every file processed.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-changes\fR
Like verbose but report only when a change is made.
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-silent\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress most error messages.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-no\-dereference\fR
Affect symbolic links instead of the files they point to.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
chown alice file.txt         Change owner to alice
chown alice:staff dir/       Change owner and group
chown :www-data web/         Change group only
chown -R root:root /etc/     Recursive chown
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR chmod (1),
.BR chgrp (1)
.SH AUTHOR
OurOS Contributors.
